    java.io.Serializable
    public class ExceptionWithMove
extends java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
    This exception is a TimeoutException which contains an int array where information can be handed over. The information mainly is used to hand over a possible move if the time is up.

      • ExceptionWithMove

        public ExceptionWithMove​(int[] posAndInfo)
        This Constructor creates an exception that contains a Position. For example this can be used when the time is up when searching for all possible moves. The Position then could represent a possible move the player could make.
        Parameters:
        posAndInfo - int array that specifies the move. (x, y, info)
